Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel the @Kiwi{1}, then cut into 1cm chunks. Zest and halve the @Lime{1/2}.

Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{1}. Halve the @Red Chilli{1} lengthways, deseed, then finely chop.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the kiwi, chilli, spring onion, lime juice, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the salsa. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Mangetout{80%g} to the pan and stir-fry until tender, ~{2-3%mins}.

Add half the @Soy Sauce{7.5%ml}, then toss to coat and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Transfer to a #bowl{}, cover to keep warm and set aside.

Wipe out the (now empty) #frying pan{} and return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Pat the @Sea Bass Fillets{2} dry with #kitchen paper{}, then season with salt and pepper.

Once hot, carefully place your sea bass into the pan, skin-side down.

> To get crispy skin on the fish, don't move it around when it's cooking skin-side down.

Cook for ~{3-4%mins} before turning over and cooking for ~{2-3%mins} on the other side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Once cooked, lower the heat and add the @Teriyaki Sauce{75%g} and remaining @Soy Sauce{7.5%ml} to the pan. Gently turn the fish to coat, then remove from the heat.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the lime zest.

Share the zesty rice and teriyaki sea bass between your bowls, spooning over any remaining sauce from the pan.

Top with the mangetout and kiwi salsa.

Enjoy!